@node "DPMS" "About energy saving monitors."
@{b}=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                              What is DPMS?
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=@{ub}



      DPMS means Display Power Management Signaling.

      There are three different levels of DPMS that you can use.

Tooltypes:
    DPMS=V   This turns the vertical sync off.   (this saves energy.)
    DPMS=H   This turns the horizontal sync off. (this saves more energy.)
    DPMS=OFF   this turns them both off.         (this is the one to use
                                                      for maximum saving.)



@{b}-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=@{ub}
@endnode


